<br>
Sure, Grand Theft Auto and Splinter Cell might have been exclusive at launch, but they eventually get released on PC and look much better at higher resolutions and with the latest graphics cards (Xbox sports a GeForce 3, and I'm afraid to ask what the PS2 has).  <br>
<br>
So if I'm going to choose a console for more casual gaming, I'm going with the one with exclusive titles like Zelda, Metriod Prime, Eternal Darkness, Resident Evil Zero, Pikman, Starfox Adventures, and all the Mario stuff.  Granted, X-box may look <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>a little</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> better, but the difference between X-box and Gamecube is tiny compared to the difference between X-box and my PC.  I'm in my 30's and the Gamecube never feels &quot;kiddie&quot; to me. <p>Wizard Jeremyah Wasabullfrog<br>
